title: Chicago Photo Guide
description:
A comprehensive look at important Chicago landmarks, this is the only guidebook that focuses on photography while still making room for informative discussions of Chicago history, architecture, and culture. Beginning with the Loop and radiating out—east to the lake, west to Oak Park, south to Hyde Park, and north to Glencoe—this book is intended to show the many sides of a diverse metropolis.

  • Format: Softcover 
  • Dimensions: 7.6 X 10.2 in.
  • Pages:  148
